name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - San Diego
address: 1355 North Harbor Drive, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: Now Open: We look forward to serving you soon.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Ruth's Chris Steak House in San Diego, CA serves the finest USDA Prime beef available, broiled at 1,800° and served on 500° plates, so your steak stays hot, juicy and delicious from first bite to last. Enjoy our New Orleans-inspired appetizers, USDA Prime steaks, fresh seafood, signature side dishes and homemade desserts. All this while you enjoy our warm, inviting atmosphere and Ruth’s Chris’ genuine hospitality. So whether you’re a regular or have just been wondering what all the buzz is about, Ruth's Chris is the perfect excuse to enjoy the perfect night out. Dinner is served nightly, reservations are suggested and private dining and offsite catering may be arranged. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />

name: Juniper & Ivy
description: Juniper and Ivy delivers a chef-driven menu that uses hand-selected, seasonal ingredients crafted with precision, passion, and creativity. Daily offerings rotate, based on the top ingredients brought in by local farmers and fishermen that morning.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />We are pleased to be able to offer our Under the Stars outdoor dining space along with our indoor Dining Room . We do our best to offer a safe and socially distant atmosphere, in both areas.  While still maintaining a comfortable and cozy al fresco experience for our outdoor guests.

name: Herb & Wood
description: A timeless, sought-after dining escape, celebrated Chef Brian Malarkey opened Herb & Wood to instant acclaim over four years ago. In that time, the restaurant has become an icon, a dining destination that has helped to propel San Diego's culinary reputation to new heights. By focusing on rustic, wood-fired dishes, Chef Malarkey's menu elevates humble ingredients such as carrots, beets, and chicken, incorporating Mediterranean flavors and a California ethos of seasonality and sustainability.\u003cbr />

name: Fogo de Chao - San Diego
description: Fogo de Chao is the leading Brazilian steakhouse specializing in fire-roasting high-quality meats since 1979 utilizing the centuries-old Southern Brazilian cooking technique of churrasco. Please join us on our patio, or bring the Fogo Experience to you with Fogo To-Go, Butcher Shop or Catering for Pick-Up or Contactless Delivery.  Visit www.fogo.com to make a reservation or place an order.

name: Barbusa
description: Barbusa Local Modern Sicilian Restaurant.\u003cbr />Lively atmosphere with our craft cocktails, handmade pastas, freshest seafood, delicate pizza, and our famous Sicilian Ribeye.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Pizza Served from our stone fired oven.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Gluten free and Vegan Items Available\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />DUE TO UNCERTAIN TIMES WE WILL NO LONGER BE TAKING RESERVATIONS.ALL EXISTING RESERVATIONS WILL BE HONORED.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />WHILE WE VALUE THE TIME OF ALL OUR LOYAL GUEST AND SMILING FACES, WE KINDLY REQUEST YOU LIMIT THE TIME SPENT AT YOUR TABLE DUE TO MANDATED REDUCTION IN CAPACITY.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />THANK YOU FOR YOUR UNDERSTANDING AND SUPPORT, WE COULDNT BE MORE THRILLED TO HAVE YOU BACK!\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />

name: Butcher’s Cut Steakhouse
description: Butchers cut is a contemporary grill and premiere steakhouse that offers an unmatched selection of beef, fish, and pasta. As the premier steakhouse of San Diego located in the heart of the Gaslamp Quarter, we offer an ambiance with a rustic and vintage vibe that takes you back to a simple and classic era. Our newly installed glass meat locker on the restaurant floor is a spectacle everyone must experience in person, where patrons can handpick the piece that catches their eye. We promise to be the freshest, most desired dining destination in the Gaslamp District. We are offering a Tuesday night date night-$79 menu for two people, from 4 PM-close

name: Civico by the Park
description: Join us for brunch starting Sunday, April 4th, and every Sunday after! Come relax by the the park with a delicious Spritz and one of Chef Pietro's Calabrifornian creations! In addition to amazing cocktails and food, enjoy a live DJ playing low tempo jams. (Brunch only)\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Civico by The Park is the new location for the famous Civico1845 in Little Italy, San Diego. The Gallo Brothers are bringing their love, passion, and enthusiasm, to Banker's Hill!\u003cbr />\u003cbr />We feature flavors of authentic Calabrian cuisine, created through surprising techniques and nuances by owner and Executive Chef Pietro Gallo.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />We offer full traditional and vegan menus with the addition of our homemade pizza in two styles: the Pinsa Romana and Calabrian Pizza!\u003cbr />\u003cbr />In addition, we offer an outstanding selection of Italian wines and craft cocktails focusing on amaro and grappa—the perfect aperitivo or complement to your meal.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Hope to see you soon!\u003cbr />Dario and Pietro Gallo

name: Nolita Hall
description: Inspired by both the modern and traditional drinking emporiums in Europe’s legendary beer cities, Nolita Hall San Diego is opening our doors with the promise of a unique and unexpected full-service restaurant experience. We are not able to seat incomplete parties or parties larger than the number on the reservation. Your entire party must be present within 15 minutes of your reservation time. All guests are required to wear a face-covering when not seated and must adhere to social distancing of 6 feet when not seated. We are following strict sanitation and social distancing protocols to ensure the safety of our guests and employees.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Note: Your table will be reserved for 2 hours.\u003cbr />

name: Rovino
description: Rovino, located in San Diego, California, offers Italian cuisine for lunch and dinner. Rovino features an extensive wine selection and a knowledgeable staff who can help pair wine with each entrée.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Try the fried calamari or the saffron rice balls filled with ground beef, peas and mozzarella cheese to start out your meal at Rovino. Choose from dinner entrées like the prosciutto and arugula flatbread or the pasta al sugo. Top off your Italian experience with a cup of specialty coffee and a dessert such as the tiramisu or the cannoli.\u003cbr />

name: Civico 1845
description: Fresh flavors with a modern spin on traditional Italian classics. Menu features several gluten-free and vegan friendly options.

name: Nonna
description: Many restaurants in Little Italy have become destinations, among them the Busalacchi family's Nonna. The rustic décor features a relaxed country-style feel throughout the restaurant, including the delightful patio. The wonderfully welcoming atmosphere celebrates yet another delicious Sicilian food lineup, including pizzas and all that you would expect from an authentic Italian menu. The terrific entrées show the Sicilian influence, and fill the restaurant with great aromas.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />We would love to hear your feedback on your experience.

name: Pali Wine Co. Little Italy Tasting Room
description: Our San Diego tasting room is located near the heart of Little Italy and is the perfect spot to enjoy our award winning wines in San Diego! Stop in to taste our Pinot Noir and Chardonnay from the Central Coast and stick around for some Cali-Tapas. This location also showcases our second and third wine labels. Tower 15, which offers premium Bordeaux and  Rhone blends alongside other varietals grown in the Central Coast region. Neighborhood Winery, specializing in interesting blends – both daring and traditional – that often push the boundaries of conventional wine flavor profiles. Our upstairs balcony overlooking Little Italy and our extremely inviting new backyard patio are both pet friendly spaces.  We offer a very unique, full service wine and food experience.

name: Zinqué - San Diego
description: Hip neighborhood restaurant with French-inspired dishes and small plates. Craft cocktail menu and uniquely curated wine and beer selection. High-design/low-key vibe for breakfast, lunch, drinks or dinner.\u003cbr />(zin-kae)

name: STK- San Diego
description: STK San Diego artfully blends two concepts into one—the modern steakhouse and a chic lounge. A large central lounge area is furnished with creamy leather banquettes, and is surrounded by an elevated dining room for more formal dining. Theatrical lights illuminate each table, large windows  allow patrons to catch a glimpse of the bustling Gaslamp Quarter, while a DJ creates an energetic vibe throughout the entire space. STK San Diego is located in the heart of Gaslamp Quarter at the Andaz San Deigo. As anticipated, steak is the main attraction. STK San Diego offers small, medium and large cuts of meat, as well as naturally raised options and market fresh fish entrees. Aside from steak, signature items include Parmesan Truffle Fries; Lil’ BRGs; Tuna Tartar; and Sweet Corn Pudding.

name: Ristorante Illando
description: From the owner Leonardo Landini \u003cbr />"When I decided to open Ristorante Illando, I had a vision in my head...my cozy house back in Firenze, Italy; my family dining table filled with the food I grew up with. Now I can surround you with the warmth of my Italian home and an authentic Italian meal here at Illando. Benvenuti e buon appetito a tutti!!"\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Located just above Little Italy San Diego's popular pizza shop, Landini's Pizzeria.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />We have a 15 minute grace period. Please call if you are running later than 15 minutes after your reservation time. The whole party must be present before all can be seated. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />A credit card is required to guarantee reservations of 10 or more. Please call hostess.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Thank you for your love and support! \u003cbr />

name: Farmer's Table - Little Italy
address: 550 W. Date St, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: Excited to announce that we officially have four locations open in San Diego including Bay Park, Little Italy, La Mesa, and Chula Vista. As a family run operation we believe every good neighborhood deserves an eatery where locals and visitors can enjoy “honest food done right”. Here at Farmers Table, we specialize in farm-to-fork cuisine that focuses on bringing locally sourced organic ingredients together to be savored in an inviting family-friendly atmosphere, where adults and children can enjoy many different food options that are just right for them. If you are looking for a magical brunch this week, come stop by for an unforgettable night.

name: Mimmo's Italian Village
address: 1743 India St, null, San Diego, CA, 92101-2517
description: Mimmos Italian Village is one of the 3 original restaurants  left in San Diego's historic Little Italy district. Established in 1973 in the heart of Little Italy you will find Mimmos is 3rd generation family owned and operated . \u003cbr />\u003cbr />Enjoy our amazing food all homemade from scratch daily, using quality  ingredients and fresh local produce . \u003cbr />\u003cbr />Our popular dishes include, campanelle sausage, spicy shrimp linguine, and chicken parmesan. You can enjoy these dishes alongside a nice glass of wine or signature homemade sangria.\u003cbr />\u003cbr /> Mimmo's Italian Village was started by Vincenzo Mimmo Gaglio, originally from Montelepre, Sicily. Before arriving in San Diego, Gaglio sharpened his cooking skills in Tunisia, New York City, Ontario, California, and finally, San Diego.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Mimmo's seating areas consist of a charming indoor village, alfresco front and back patio seating.

name: Brigantine at Portside Pier
address: 1360 N Harbor Dr, San Diego, CA, 92101-3322
description:
The Brigantine is more than just home to some of San Diego’s finest seafood. It’s a place where locals and visitors alike come to share a lively atmosphere and authentic sense of community. The Morton family opened the first Brigantine on Shelter Island in 1969, with a vision that embraced the beach town lifestyle, a dedication to flavorful food, and a passion for friendly service.

Today, we’re known far and wide for our San Diego-style surf and turf. From our award-winning fish tacos and freshly shucked oysters, to classic filet mignon or our perpetually best-selling marinated grilled swordfish. Always prepared to exceed expectations, and served with a smile. You can stop in at any neighborhood Brigantine and get a taste of the local flavor, from regionally inspired specials, to custom cocktails and home town craft beers.

At the Brigantine we make first timers feel like regulars, and consider regulars part of the family. So come by often, and share our taste for life.

name: Allegro
description: Sicilian born Executive Chef Marco Provino, is a master in the kitchen, constantly shocking us with his latest creations. Our see through glass allows patrons to have a full view of the kitchen to ensure no shortcuts are ever taken.  As the sexiest restaurant in Little Italy, we offer an exquisite yet youthful ambience including a beautiful lemon garden patio covered in velvet, gold, marble, ceramic tiles, and couture fire pits that make Allegro perfect for a special occasion with your significant other. As part of the San Diego Dining Group, we take every step to uphold sky-high standards and quality to ensure the most magical dining experience. Join us for happy hour Sunday to Thursday 4pm-6pm. $5 draft beer and fresh oysters.

name: Petrini's
address: 610 W Ash St, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: Petrini's, in the heart of San Diego's Little Italy neighborhood, serves homemade Italian dishes with a traditional aesthetic in its charming and inviting restaurant. The diablo shrimp in spicy wing sauce with lemon and cream, served with garlic cheese bread makes the perfect starter to your meal. Some of Petrini's' specialty entrée dishes include the smoked salmon alfredo sautéed with tomatoes and basil, Petrini's flat iron steak marinated in Italian beer, garlic and rosemary served with spaghetti with tangy pomodoro sauce and the baked white fish tilapia coated in seasoned bread crumbs in wine, butter and garlic sauce with Tuscan vegetables. Handhelds, such as the classic meatball hoagie, the vegetarian caponata sandwich with tomato-stewed eggplant and the craft-your-own pizzas, are other diner favorites.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />For a sweet end to your meal at Petrini's, enjoy a homemade classic Italian dessert, the layered tiramisu cake.\u003cbr />

name: Isola Little Italy
description: MY NONNA’S NAME WAS ISOLA, A WONDERFUL COOK WHO GAVE ME A PASSION FOR FOOD AND FRESH, SIMPLE INGREDIENTS.  \u003cbr />\u003cbr />I have vivid memories of my grandmother turning plain bread into amazing desserts, simple apples into incredible fritters sprinkled with a little sugar and honey, and even treating my sunburns with olive oil. Thirty years later, I still savor every meal and moment.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Isola is proud to serve the finest local ingredients, dalla vite, from the vine. I hope you enjoy every bite, plucked from my family tree for your table. Buon appetito!

name: Del Frisco’s Double Eagle Steakhouse - San Diego
address: 901 Bayfront Court, Suite 105, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: Del Frisco’s Double Eagle Steakhouse embodies the rich tradition of the classic American steakhouse, serving USDA Prime Beef, fresh seafood and premium wines from our award-winning wine selection in a breathtaking atmosphere.

name: Parc Bistro-Brasserie
description: Listed as one of OpenTable’s “100 Best Neighborhood Gems in America for 2021”

name: Topside Terrace
address: 421 W B St, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: \u003cbr />A quintessential San Diego open-air terrace, Topside Terrace takes advantage of the San Diego climate while marrying the sites and sounds of downtown. Inspired by coastal living, we specialize in evening fare and weekend brunch serving Baja California and Classic American Fare paired with contemporary cocktails and draft beer.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Happy hour every Sunday-Thursday from 4pm to 6pm!\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Live DJ every Saturday 6pm-10pm

name: Eddie V's - Seaport District
address: 789 West Harbor Drive, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: OUR PATIO IS OPEN. CURBSIDE PICKUP AVAILABLE – Our patio is open, but we are delighted to still offer takeout. Visit EddieV.com/takeout or call (619) 615-0281 to place an order.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />If you're looking for a stylish and sophisticated fine dining experience, join us at Eddie V’s in San Diego. Dishes are artistically prepared and feature an ever-changing array of seasonal seafood, along with critically acclaimed prime steaks, hand-carved and broiled to perfection. Our restaurant’s award-wining wine list, which has been recognized by Wine Spectator, has more than 300 wines from the best growing areas in California and around the world. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />Polite Dress Notice - To promote a family friendly and welcoming atmosphere for everyone. We consider gym attire, sweatpants, hats, clothing with offensive languages or images, and exposed undergarments too casual for our restaurants.

name: Island Prime
address: 880 Harbor Island Drive, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: Resting on stilts atop San Diego Bay, Island Prime overlooks the city skyline and Coronado.

name: Claim Jumper - San Diego - Bayside
address: 1355 North Harbor Drive, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: Our friendly environment is ideal for celebrating special occasions, hosting a business lunch or gathering for a delicious meal with friends and family. Our saloons are a comfortable gathering place to relax after a day at work, to catch a game or share an appetizer with friends. The saloon menu features signature cocktails, chilled martinis, premium and ultra-premium spirits, specialty non-alcoholic beverages, an extensive wine list, and imported and American craft beers including Claim Jumper’s own Honey Blonde, Original Red Ale and IPA.  In addition to the saloon menu Claim Jumper offers a Steakhouse menu which includes USDA Prime steaks and premium house made shareable sides. Open daily for lunch and dinner, Claim Jumper offers a selection of freshly prepared items using only the finest ingredients available. Favorites include Certified Angus Beef®, fresh fish, baby back pork ribs, fresh baked pot pie, specialty salads, pasta, sandwiches, burgers and more.

name: Puesto at the Headquarters
address: 789 W. Harbor Dr., San Diego, CA, 92101
description:
Owned and operated by a Mexican American family whose best memories all include tacos, Puesto is an award-winning Mexican Artisan Kitchen & Bar providing an innovative approach to authentic Mexican flavors. Puesto has garnered national acclaim for its Mexico City-style crispy melted cheese tacos, served on handmade non-GMO, organic, maíz azul stone-ground tortillas. 

In addition to tacos, offerings include a selection of fresh catch ceviches, guacamoles, starters and ensaladas, courtesy of Chef/Partner Luisteen Gonzales. The bar program showcases the best of Mexico City through the use of fresh ingredients in our hand crafted cocktails and housemade Micheladas, tequilas, mezcals, Baja craft beers, and Valle de Guadalupe wines you can’t find elsewhere 

We’re honored to have been featured by media outlets nationally and internationally, some of which include National Geographic, Huffington Post, Refinery 29, MSN, Insider, Zagat, Eater, Food and Wine, and LA Times.

name: Water Grill - San Diego
description: Located steps away from Petco Park in the heart of Downtown San Diego, Water Grill is a true seafood destination. Family owned and operated, Water Grill focuses on first-of-the-season seafood and has delivered a superior dining experience for more than 30 years. Their devotion to quality seafood sourced in-house, is illustrated on their daily menus.\u003cbr /> \u003cbr />Sourcing from local fishermen, Water Grill’s seafood arrives from boat to table in a matter of hours. Water Grill Executive Chefs prepare the dishes with care, allowing the fresh seafood to shine, while using high-quality ingredients to elevate the recipe. From Spiny Lobsters in the fall to Wild Salmon in the spring, Water Grill’s focus is all about local, sustainable seafood and a one-of-a-kind experience. \u003cbr /> \u003cbr />A safe and comfortable experience, Water Grill follows all the CDC guidelines to ensure you have an amazing experience each and every time.

name: Cowboy Star
description: Located in the heart of the East Village neighborhood of San Diego, Cowboy Star is dedicated to providing an unmatched attention to detail and a level of service that immediately sets us apart.  Cowboy Star guests are the number one priority and guest satisfaction is the base upon which our entire concept is built. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />Our level of service is only matched by our celebration of regional American heirloom recipes offered with genuine neighborly hospitality.  We are committed to supporting local and regional farmers, fishers and producers by cooking food that recaptures the simple and pure tastes found in locally grown, natural and organic ingredients.  We strive to raise awareness of a more sustainable food future, while helping to restore a sense of community that brings us back to a more homegrown time.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />The Cowboy Star Menu features the finest in select natural products including Niman Ranch all natural beef from the nation's leading Certified Humane Angus herd.

name: Barrio Star
description:
The sky’s the limit at Barrio Star--presenting San Diego with modern Mexican Soul Food woven with bold Latin flavors and clever Asian touches. 

As one of several restaurants created by award-winning chef and restaurateur Isabel Cruz, Barrio Star’s bright and lively décor is a metaphor for what we proudly serve. Our vibrant flavors and healthier renditions of classic Mexican dishes reveal thoughtfully presented menu items that are sure to please every palate. 

Pairing with our well-prepared food is a mouthwatering beer and cocktail menu. Besides serving standard Mexican beers, we also offer rotating drafts as well as an extensive tequila menu. Kickstart the evening with our roasted jalapeno blackberry margarita and let the fiesta begin!

name: The Lion's Share
description: In addition to modern American fare, The Lion's Share features exotic meats seldom found in other restaurants.  The menu pairs well with an interesting wine list focused around small production wineries.  \u003cbr>\u003cbr />Last, but not least, they offer hand-crafted cocktails considered amongst the best in the city in an eclectic atmosphere with a friendly staff.

name: The Melting Pot - Gaslamp Quarter
description: Welcome to The Melting Pot  San Diego Gaslamp\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Located on 5th Ave & E St in the historic Gaslamp Plaza Suites, the San Diego - Gaslamp Melting Pot Restaurant brings a truly unique, romantic and interactive four-course fondue dining experience to San Diego's vibrant downtown dining scene.!

name: Monzu Fresh Pasta
description: We are Monzu Fresh Pasta, a fast-casual eatery serving Italian and contemporary flavors made from scratch in the heart of San Diego’s East Village. In drawing upon our European heritage and passion for hand-crafted meals, we take pride in transporting you to Italy via our home country’s most beloved staple: fresh pasta.

name: Lionfish Restaurant at The Pendry Hotel
description:
The taste of fresh sustainable seafood has come to the Gaslamp Quarter.
Lionfish, located in the Pendry San Diego, is a modern, cutting edge restaurant located on 5th Avenue that features fresh-catch cuisine and seasonal ingredients, all prepared with innovative twists by homegrown San Diego chef JoJo Ruiz.
The two-story space takes San Diego seafood restaurants to the next level and will honor the essence of the city’s lifestyle with a menu that is both hip and healthy, eccentric but not excessive.
Having studied under Michelin star and celebrity chefs, Ruiz has developed a network of fisherman and produce growers to ensure that the Lionfish kitchen uses only the freshest and most seasonal ingredients…

name: Osteria Panevino
description: Osteria Panevino is the oldest restaurant in all of the Gaslamp Quarter that features the best Italian cuisine that San Diego has to offer, winning the gold awards for best family restaurant in San Diego, and best Italian Cuisine in San Diego that will surely have your taste buds blown away. Our world renowned chef, Vincenzo Lo Verso, has spent over 25 years perfecting his Sicilian recipes, following age-old family traditions that have withstood the test of time. Stop by and surround yourself in a rustic, Tuscan ambience as chef Vincenzo takes you on a culinary adventure of a lifetime.

name: Lou & Mickey's
description: Located across the street from the San Diego Convention Center and nestled underneath the iconic entrance to the Gaslamp Quarter, Lou & Mickey’s has been Downtown San Diego’s favorite steakhouse for over a decade. The restaurant was recently renovated, yet still magically transports you to another time. Whether you’re a Ribeye fanatic or a Wagyu lover, this timeless steakhouse is a true meat destination.

name: Asti Ristorante
description: Since 1994, Asti has been serving locals and visitors authentic Italian cuisine in a unique and inviting atmosphere.  Whether you dine on our lively patio, or choose to sit inside and enjoy the beautiful artwork and brick walls, you're sure to have an unforgettable dining experience.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Each dish on our menu, from our selection of antipasti, handmade pastas, fresh seafood, and quality steaks, is inspired by the delicious flavors of Northern Italy.  While some restaurants offer small plates, Asti continues to serve up delicious abundance, all freshly and individually prepared to order.  With an extensive vintage wine selection and knowledgeable staff, we deliver a true Italian dining experience that will leave your palate asking for more!\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />

name: Edgewater Grill
address: 861 West Harbor Dr, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: Edgewater Grill is located in Seaport Village, on downtown San Diego's Bay. We have one of the finest waterfront views in San Diego! Spanning the length of the restaurant are outdoor patios where guests can enjoy an unobstructed view of the Coronado Bridge and Island.

name: Mad House
description: Welcome to Mad House! Home of the biggest menu in the Gaslamp Quarter. We're open late :)

name: Nobu San Diego
description: World renowned for its award winning \New Style\ Japanese cuisine

name: Sugar Factory American Brasserie - Theatre Box
description: Sugar Factory is known the world over for its celebrity-endorsed Couture Pops, which have turned sweets into the latest designer accessory. We now have locations in some of the world’s most cosmopolitan cities, including Las Vegas, New York City, Bahrain, Chicago, Miami, Dubai, Orlando and Manila.\r\n\r\nIconic superstars including Kylie Jenner, Kendall Jenner, Britney Spears, Drake, Nicole Scherzinger, Kim Kardashian, Eva Longoria and Rupert Grint are just a few of the celebrities who have either endorsed or have been spotted with the sparkly lollipops. Sugar Factory’s loyal celebrity following has received widespread media attention from People Magazine, the Daily Mail, US Weekly, Entertainment Tonight, Extra and more.

name: Albert's Restaurant - San Diego Zoo
description: Located in the heart of the San Diego Zoo, Albert’s offers full-service dining where you can enjoy deck seating with the ambiance of a tropical waterfall.  Patio seating not guaranteed!\u003cbr />\u003cbr />The menu features a variety of unique dishes including seafood specialties, a variety of entrees, salads, sandwiches, and children’s options. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />Join us for Weekend Brunch on Saturdays and Sundays from 10:00 am to 12:00 pm.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Valid San Diego Zoo Membership or admission ticket is required to dine in Alberts Restaurant.\u003cbr />

name: Gyu-kaku - Downtown San Diego
description: We are open for limited dine-in service.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />We have updated our operations in accordance with all government guidelines to put your health and safety first.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />To maintain a safe environment for you and Gyu-Kaku staff, we ask that all guests understand and adhere to the following:\u003cbr />\u003cbr />- Masks are recommended\u003cbr />- There may be limits on party sizes.\u003cbr />- We are serving a limited menu. Not all Grand Menu items will be available during our immediate reopening.\u003cbr />- We only accept payment via credit or debit card. Cash payments respectfully declined.\u003cbr />

name: Gaslamp Fish House
description: Gaslamp Fish House is opened. Our Guests and employee's safety is our main concern. We are taking extra action to keep everyone safe.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />We are offering a unique fusion of Mediterranean and American Cuisine.  Our Oyster bar, Fresh Fish and Seafood, as well as all our Black Angus Grass Fed Beef are sourced locally from sustainable San Diego Fisheries and California Farms. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />Come to check us, seat and relax, our Team will do the rest.

name: Barrel & Board Social
description: A New Woman-Forward Intimate Cocktail & Food Experience is Here!\u003cbr />Welcome to Hillcrest’s chicest spot for craft cocktails, barrel-aged potables, and chef-inspired shareable boards. An upscale LGBTQ+ bar, restaurant & event space brought to you by the Mo’s Universe Group! \u003cbr />Named San Diego's Top 10 Hottest Cocktail spots by EATER, as well as Open Table's Top 10 DINERS CHOICE Winner! \u003cbr />

name: Fleming's Steakhouse - San Diego
description: Fleming's Prime Steakhouse & Wine Bar is an outstanding choice to enjoy an exceptional Prime steak, glass of wine or handcrafted cocktail. Whether you’re celebrating a special occasion, hosting a business dinner or simply wanting to enjoy an excellent culinary experience  – we will create a safe and memorable evening for you. If you prefer to enjoy your fine dining experience at home, you can order and pay for lunch or dinner online and then pick up curbside or select from one of our delivery partners.

name: Greystone Prime Steakhouse & Seafood
description: Greystone Prime Steakhouse & Seafood has been a landmark destination in the historic Gaslamp Quarter in Downtown San Diego for 20 years. As a family-owned restaurant with family values that is dedicated to the highest level of service, we were honored when we were recognized as being one of the top 10 steakhouses in California. Our wide selection of USDA prime meat, and exotic game is surely going to have you taste buds begging for more. We offer an elegant and classic ambiance made perfect with the beautiful lighting, setting a romantic mood for a date night. Come stop by for our world famous wagyu and espresso martinis for a once-in-a-lifetime experience

name: Operacaffe
description: At Operacaffe we are passionate about  our culinary business and our customers.  The reputation for excellent cuisine, top-notch service, the quality and freshness of ingredients are the reasons we are so proud of our brand new restaurant!

name: Cerveza Jack's Gaslamp
description: Located in the Gaslamp District of San Diego, Cerveza Jack's is an everyday escape for any food & drink lover. Our menu features Southern comfort favorites inspired by our sister location in “Music City” Nashville, TN, while maintaining the effortless cool of the California coast. Perfect for a Lunch in the San Diego sun or a night of drunken debauchery (or both), Cerveza Jack's promises to be an oasis complete with live music, big personality and memories to be made.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />**All checks will have a 4% pandemic recovery surcharge due to the additional costs associated with the impact on our business and operations. This is not a gratuity and will be used to help us offset the additional product, labor, overhead and other costs.**

name: La Bonne Table
description: LA BONNE TABLE is a cozy and intimate restaurant in the heart of the bustling neighborhood of Hillcrest. We serve country french food in a bistro fashion. Our menu consists of classic french dishes, a modest but excellent selection that will change with the seasons. We offer a romantic atmosphere and elegant setting, full bar and french beer on tap. Reservations are recommended as seating is very limited in this exclusive restaurant. ​Bon Appetit!

name: Bandar Restaurant
description: \u003cbr />For dining:\u003cbr />Monday - Thursday: 4:00pm to 9:00pm\u003cbr />Friday: 4:00pm to 10:00pm\u003cbr />Saturday: 1:30pm to 10:00pm\u003cbr />Sunday: 1:30pm to 9:00pm\u003cbr />\u003cbr />We are open for Takeout  everyday   \u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Bandar Restaurant serves Mediterranean food with unique Persian spices flown to San Diego and served in original recipes. Chefs Behrooz and Shokooh create simple preparations to showcase them, alongside an exotic variety of oven-roasted eggplant, charbroiled chicken, seafood and flavorful prime steaks. Look for signature classics such as Nadari, Barg and Soltani. Bandar Restaurant is award-winning since 1996. The restaurant has a unique energy, sitting right in the heart of Gaslamp Quarter in Downtown San Diego.

name: The Rooftop by STK
description: We are currently offering, order at the bar style service for food and drinks with OPEN SEATING.  Reservations are not required to access the Rooftop.  \u003cbr />\u003cbr />Please note that the menu from STK Restaurant (lobby level) is not available on the Rooftop.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />For parties larger than 8 or cabana rentals, please email ly.costales@andaz.com\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />\u003cbr />

name: The Red Door
address: 741 W. Washington St., San Diego, CA, 92103
description: The Red Door San Diego is committed to offering our guests sustainable and responsibly sourced farm-to-fork dishes. We proudly serve contemporary Italian and modern European cuisine with the freshest locally grown and handcrafted products available. We also feature delicious and unique ingredients from around the world. Chef/Owner Luciano Cibelli shops daily, personally selecting every item we serve. He bakes fresh breads, rolls, desserts and all of the pasta in house (including a special Gluten Free Bucatini) and he develops his menus in rhythm with the seasonal San Diego harvest.  Enjoy nightly special offerings or a house favorite, Beef Wellington. Join us for the highly rated cuisine and return for the charming ambiance and excellent service behind the Red Door.

name: Saltwater
description: Saltwater is the premiere seafood restaurant in the Gaslamp Quarter, owned by the SD Dining group. As the best seafood restaurant in San Diego, we pride ourselves on the freshness of our ingredients, with fish being flown in daily from the mediteranean sea straight to our fresh fish bar where diners can choose their fish, weigh it and have it cooked to perfection, exactly how they like it! This is one of the few restaurants in California that offers this kind of seafood experience and truly sets us apart from our competition. The interior is a stunning deep royal blue that offers a romantic, premier, and nautical ambience that will make you feel like you are on a 90’ Riva yacht sailing through the Grand Canal. Come stop by for an experience that you will surely never forget.

name: Peohe's - Coronado Waterfront Restaurant
description: Nestled on Coronado Island, offers spectacular waterfront views of the San Diego Skyline just across the bay. Famous for fresh fish, seafood, steaks, prime rib and other Island-inspired cuisine. 3 Hour Parking Validation when you dine with Peohe's.

name: Union Kitchen & Tap - Gaslamp
description: The Vibe\u003cbr />\u003cbr />A little more than a stone’s throw from its original digs in Encinitas, Union Kitchen & Tap ignites the Gaslamp with our second neighborhood-friendly dining and drinking destination. Seamlessly melding refined and rustic, vintage and contemporary. Stylish without being sleek, Union Kitchen & Tap is warm and inviting, comfortable and lively.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Union Kitchen & Tap boasts impressive surroundings of reclaimed wood and modern furnishings bringing their Americana concept to life, along with garage-style doors that open up to a generous patio, connecting Union’s bustling indoor vibe with refreshing outdoor spaces. Live entertainment and weekend DJs always set the stage for a great night out.

name: Pushkin Russian Restaurant
description: Pushkin Restaurant proudly bears the name in honor of the great Russian writer Alexander Pushkin (May 26, 1799 - January 29, 1837) - Russian poet, play and prose writer, critic, literary theorist, historian, a publicist who laid the foundations of the Russian realistic trend.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Since our opening in October 2015, we have focused on bringing out the authenticity and deep history of Russian cuisine through our traditional and family recipes. At Pushkin, we pay tribute to the Russian as well as former Soviet Union cuisines from counties such as Ukraine, Armenia, Uzbekistan and Georgia which had a tremendous impact on what is considered Russian cuisine today. We believe this notion creates both unique and new dishes for you to try out!

name: Harley Gray Kitchen & Bar
address: 902 West Washington St, San Diego, CA, 92103
description: Harley Gray kitchen & bar is located on the corner of Goldfinch St. and Washington St. with outside patio seating on both sides, includes heaters and has an open sliding glass door wall.  We offer breakfast, lunch and dinner as well as an amazing weekend Brunch Menu with items including a Lobster Benedict, Organic Acai Bowl and Spicy Chiliquiles and you can take advantage of the $10 free flowing mimosas! \u003cbr />\u003cbr />We are known for many of our fantastic weekly specials at Harley Gray: Wednesday Night neighborhood night which offers Happy Hour all night, Thursday night Live Maine Lobster and Friday night Slow Roast Prime Rib to mention some more popular ones.  We strive to offer you an amazing dining experience that includes incredible food, unique and fun cocktails and of course friendly professional service from our entire staff.

name: Blind Burro
description: The Blind Burro specializes in fresh, coastal Baja Mexican cuisine.  Our emphasis is on quality, from the customer service, to the ingredients we use in all of our hand crafted food and drinks.  We want our guests to enjoy Baja Mexican fare right here in East Village, San Diego.  Come in and enjoy a relaxed atmosphere where you can meet over a carafe of spicy margaritas or on tap house sangria. .  Or try us for lunch with clients while enjoying steak tacos and a quinoa mixed green salad.   Hope to see you soon in the unique, airy and comfortable environment we have created for you in downtown San Diego. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />**All checks will have a 4% pandemic recovery surcharge due to the additional costs associated with the impact on our business and operations.  This is not a gratuity and will be used to help us offset the additional product, labor, overhead and other costs.**

name: il Sogno Italiano
description: An unforgettable dining and musical soiree awaits you as we transport you to a Nostalgic yet modern Americana meets old world ambiance, perfect for any occasion.  Our music program features world class entertainers and touring artists 7 nights a week, paired with an array of specialty craft cocktails and wines from across Italy and the California Coast. Our kitchen uses fresh sustainable ingredients and specializes in California Coastal Italian Cuisine with handmade pizzas, pastas, steaks and seafood. Our Mezzanine accommodates up to 100 guests and we offer a private bar, TV's upon request for private events and meeting spaces. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />We look forward to hosting you at Il Sogno Italiano and Welcome you to San Diegos hottest place for fine dining and music. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />Mondays: Martinis & Jazz w/Grammy Nominated Sacha Boutros and friends/Martini specials all night long\u003cbr />Wednesdays: Passport to Italy \u003cbr />Pop, Jazz, RnB, Motown and beyond every night of the week.

name: Farmer's Bottega Restaurant
address: 860 West Washington Street, San Diego, CA, 92103
description: Farm-to-table restaurant located in the heart of Mission Hills.  Farmer's Bottega serves farm fresh breakfast, brunch, lunch, and dinner along with a unique selection of craft local beer and wine.

name: Tom Hams Lighthouse
address: 2150 Harbor Island Dr, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: Tom Ham’s Lighthouse was built in 1971 by a man who was not afraid to put his name on his product. Rooted in warm welcomes & excellent food, Tom Ham made his lifelong dream a reality. Tom Ham’s Lighthouse is the only restaurant in the US to have a USCG operated & maintained Lighthouse attached to it. You can locate us on any modern nautical map as Beacon #9. Featuring a 100% responsibly resourced seafood menu & award winning Sunday Champagne Brunch, we are a must when it comes to the San Diego food scene. The dining room, purposely shaped like the state of California, allows for groups as grand as 50 yet private enough for a couple’s night out. Holiday brunches have been long time family traditions for many San Diegans. Start your family’s tradition this next holiday. With the best views of the Downtown City Skyline, Coronado & San Diego Bay, Tom Ham's is & remains a San Diego tradition in dining excellence since 1971.

name: Buca di Beppo - San Diego
description: If you are looking for an Italian Restaurant in San Diego, CA then come to Buca. We are located at the corner of Sixth Avenue and G Street and proudly serve authentic family style Italian dishes. We specialize in celebrations and also offer catering suitable for all occasions.

name: Ortega's  A Mexican Bistro
description: Ortega’s Mexican Bistro features the authentic flavors of Puerto Nuevo. Experience Baja style lobster and table side guacamole while sipping one of our classic fresh squeezed margaritas. Enjoy dining in our restaurant or for a more energized evening, dine in our bar - La Cantina. Additional flavors include Banana Crusted Huachinango, Flat Iron Steak Burrito, Chicken Mole.  The design captures the festive traditions and tasteful flavors of Puerto Nuevo and Baja California.

name: El Agave
address: 2304 San Diego Ave., null, San Diego, CA, 92110
description: Experience the true flavor of Mexico at San Diego’s premier Mexican cuisine destination.\u003cbr />Established in 1996, El Agave Restaurant & Tequileria offers its patrons a unique dining setting within\u003cbr />the largest tequila museum in the United States – with over 2,700 tequilas on display – also\u003cbr />repeatedly voted the #1 tequila bar in the country. Nestled in historic Old Town, San Diego, it is the\u003cbr />perfect place to enjoy a business lunch, romantic date, rehearsal dinner or to simply relax and\u003cbr />unwind sipping find tequila with friends. \u003cbr />

name: Fifth and Rose at Pendry San Diego
description: A SOPHISTICATED WATERING HOLE WITH ELEVATED BAR FARE     \u003cbr />The Pendry San Diego hotel bar, Fifth & Rose, is a classic cocktail bar in an elegant, chic, and comfortable room. A classic setting for a fitting drink, it is a place to engage in conversation, enjoy bar fare, and linger over the perfect cocktail. Rich stone stands out amidst a black and white palette with crimson details, while candles and fresh roses accent tables. Fifth & Rose is inspired by a host’s living room: comfortable, always welcoming, a place you never want to leave.

name: Rich's Day Lounge
description: Rich’s is San Diego’s largest and most popular gay nightclub. Reservations are for our outdoor lounge. For VIP booths inside the nightclub text 619-578-9349. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />We have booths and cabanas for up to 15 guests. Space for larger groups and extended reservations times are available upon request.

name: Social Tap
address: 815 J St Suite #101, San Diego, CA, 92101
description: Welcome to your new favorite pregame. Social Tap San Diego sits at the edge of Petco Park, and is the perfect place for Padres fans, locals, and visitors alike to gather for high quality cocktails and bites. This elevated bar scene takes the best of sports bars to a new level, bringing you an incredible dining experience while you cheer for your favorite team.

name: Au Revoir
address: 420 Robinson Ave, Suite A, San Diego, CA, 92103
description: Located in the heart of Hillcrest

name: The Henry - Coronado
description: Welcome to the greatest neighborhood restaurant, a place where you can always count on a warm welcome from baristas, servers and bartenders who know your order by heart. A fusion of industrial and classical influences, our open dining spaces are bursting with charm and energy. Come and go with ease for your morning coffee, enjoy lunch with a colleague, gather the family together for dinner, or treat yourself to a post-work drink at the bar. For craveable eats and downright delicious cocktails, look no further than a place where you'll always be among friends, a place that feels like home: The Henry.

name: Rosemary Trattoria
description: Rosemary Trattoria \u003cbr />Italian Restaurant in CORONADO

name: The Presley
description: The Presley is a dynamic outdoor restaurant located in Liberty Station. A great place to gather, The Presley features classic American fare, local seafood, and unique shareable options, as well as an extensive cocktail list that includes frozen drinks, a dole whip mimosa and more!  You can always take advantage of the beautiful San Diego weather on our expansive patios complete with lush greenery, fire pits and swinging benches. It's always good to see you at The Presley!\u003cbr />\u003cbr />*STARTING 7/31/2021, Weekend Brunch will be first come first serve (no reservations). All reservations made prior to 7/31 will be honored. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />**All checks will have a 4% pandemic recovery surcharge due to the additional costs associated with the impact on our business and operations. This is not a gratuity and will be used to help us offset the additional product, labor, overhead and other costs.**

name: Madison
description: Mediterranean-inspired fare and elegant cocktails are served in sleek surroundings at this modern, airy University Heights hangout. ~Zagat

name: Tavola Nostra Pizzeria E Cucina
address: 1040 University Ave, Ste B101, San Diego, CA, 92103
description: Now Open! Tavola Nostra Pizzeria E Cucina is a full-service

name: Suckerfree Southern Plate & Bar
description: The term “soul food” didn’t become common until the 1960s. With the rise of the civil rights and black nationalist movements during the 1960s, many Black Americans sought to reclaim their part of the American cultural legacy. As terms like soul brother, soul sister and soul music were taking hold, it was only natural that the term soul food would be used to describe the recipes that Black Americans had been cooking for generations. Soul food is basic, down-home cooking with its roots in the rural South. Where the conversations are long, food is cooked slow and the drinks are cold and sweet. To many, all that just sounds like a description of Southern food. The distinctions between Soul & Southern are hard to make. While all Soul food is Southern food, not all Southern food has Soul. Soul food & Southern food cooking are examples of how great Southern cooks cooked with what they had available to them. Suckerfree will always pay homage to both traditions and remain loyal to the soil. SF

name: Nason's Beer Hall
description: A new addition to San Diego’s iconic craft beer scene, Nason’s features an expansive selection of local and international beers, globally inspired comfort food, and vintage bar games. Its name pays homage to Nason & Co. Farmer’s Market, which occupied this unique space in the early 1900s. Now offering brunch every Saturday and Sunday!

name: Storyhouse Spirits
description: We are ALL STORYTELLERS!  We founded Storyhouse Spirits on the belief that friendships grow together, share memories, and toast to our lives. While it looks like we’re just meticulously crafting small batch spirits in San Diego’s East Village, we’re secretly doing our part creating a more unified community. Bring your friends and make some new ones. Let’s all sip to the lives we share!

name: Tahona Bar
address: 2414 San Diego Ave, San Diego, CA, 92110
description: We are welcoming parties of up to 6 for indoor and outdoor dining!\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Parties of 7 or more, please email our large party coordinator at events@tahonabar.com\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Welcome to Tahona! We are the first mezcal bar and tasting room in San Diego. In our restaurant, we invite you to taste our incredible craft cocktails and our amazing contemporary Mexican cuisine featuring Oaxacan bites. In our tasting room, we welcome you to indulge on a mezcal tasting experience! \u003cbr />\u003cbr />We are located next one of the most iconic historical landmark: the Campo Santo Cemetery in Old Town. Inside Tahona, you will be transported to a modern Mexican hacienda designed with hand painted tiles, handmade rope seats, traditionally crafted fabric brought from Oaxaca, hand clayed walls and more.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />We also have a cozy covered outdoor patio dining experience so you will have the choice to dine inside our hacienda or on the streets of Old Town!

name: Jack & Giulio's Italian Restaurant
address: 2391 San Diego Ave, San Diego, CA, 92110
description: Jack and Giulio's Italian restaurant has remained a favorite of San Diegans for many years. This popular restaurant

name: Puesto Mission Valley
address: 5010 Mission Center Rd, San Diego, CA, 92108
description: Puesto is family-owned and operated by first generation Mexican American brothers Eric, Alan and Alex Adler, alongside their cousins Isidoro and Moy Lombrozo and founding chef and partner Luisteen Gonzalez. With six locations in California, Puesto provides an innovative and contemporary approach to authentic Mexican cuisine. Sourcing its ingredients locally and regionally, the restaurant has earned national acclaim for its Mexico City-inspired tacos made with non-GMO organic, heirloom Masienda blue corn stone-ground tortillas, crispy melted cheese and scratch salsas.

name: Nicolosi's on 5th
description: Coming Soon!

name: Trattoria Don Pietro
address: 2415 San Diego Ave, San Diego, CA, 92110-2801
description: Thanks to Trattoria Don Pietro, there is finally something new and fresh happening in Old Town. After spending a lifetime of cooking Italian food and a few years in LA learning from the best restaurants in the industry, Pietro is finally ready to roll up his sleeves and show San Diego his take on traditional Italian cuisine with a trendy twist. Between our groundbreaking Italian menu, wisteria garden patio ambiance, and over-the-top cocktails, we stand alone as the most instagrammable restaurant in San Diego. Come stop by today and experience our delicate balance of tradition and trend.

name: Rockin Baja Lobster Old Town
description: Rockin' Baja is a full service and fun Mexican-Seafood restaurant that offers uniquely prepared Baja style seafood presented in rustic steel buckets. We created a diverse menu filled with exceptionally great, finger lickin’ good fun food delivered fresh to your table daily.  Kick back, drink an ice cold beer or margarita, enjoy a shot of tequila and experience all the good times that are Rockin’ Baja.

name: Casa De Freds
address: 2470 San Diego Ave, San Diego, CA, 92110
description: ABOUT FREDS OLD TOWN | Since 2001, Casa de Freds in Old Town has been bringing the fiesta to San Diego. Freds is the place for amigos - both new and old - to have a great time while enjoying quality food, fresh margaritas and a festive atmosphere. The menu offers a wide variety of delicious, Baja-infused selections that are made from fresh, high-quality ingredients. The vibrant decor and great music provide a unique dining experience right in the heart of historic Old Town. The restaurant offers plenty of versatility for groups of many sizes. The large outdoor patio is dog friendly, so bring in your furry friends and check out the doggy menu! The outdoor bar is a fantastic spot to enjoy the San Diego sun, whether you are here for the weekend or live down the street. Freds newly renovated Fiesta Cantina is the perfect place to watch your favorite sporting events. The Cantina also offers daily specials that will keep your tummies, glasses and pockets full. Thanks Amigo!

name: Solare Ristorante Lounge
description: Authentic Italian - OPEN for Dine-In on our two patios - and Take-out, Curbside, and Delivery.  Solare is selected a Michelin Guide Bib Gourmand restaurant - Voted Best Italian Restaurant & Best Wine List by San Diego Magazine. Full Bar - Craft Cocktails. Family-owned and operated, Randy Smerik and his team work hard to offer an amazing dining experience for you. We believe in the use of local fresh organic produce, natural meat and wild seafood and we are a Sustainable Green Restaurant. Each dish is prepared from scratch with love and passion to satisfy our customer's heart and soul. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />Housed in the filming location for Top Gun, Solare helps to sustain the historical landmarks of San Diego's NTC Promenade. \u003cbr />

name: Et Voila! Bistro
address: 3015 Adams Ave., Suite A., San Diego, CA, 92116
description: Et Voilà! is a vibrant neighborhood bistro, located along the North Park corridor. Et Voilà! French Bistro showcases Chef Vincent Viale’s talents, mixing French classics with a modern accent. Find local and seasonal products building upon French recipes from various regions, such as Steak Frites, Coquilles St. Jacques, and soufflés. Explore the diverse regions of France through a curated wine list, and taste a variety of distinct local ingredients with our crafted cocktails. Et Voila! French Bistro is the destination for those looking for a vibrant dining experience, or even for those looking for a simple glass of wine and informal bite at the bar.\u003cbr />Feel free to call us if you cannot see your desired reservation time. We might be able to help. \u003cbr />No reservations accepted for happy hour thank you. \u003cbr />

name: True Food Kitchen - San Diego FV
description: True Food Kitchen in San Diego is currently open with dine-in and carry-out service. As always, we will continue to prioritize the health and safety of our guests by following the guidance of the CDC and local health officials. We appreciate your patience and understanding as we navigate this new normal together.

name: Alexander's on 30th
description: Family owned and operated Italian-American restaurant with San Diego award winning pizza and the most romantic patio dining in North Park. Make your reservation today and feel free to check our website or call the restaurant for more information.

name: Stake Chophouse & Bar
description: Prominently situated in the heart of Coronado’s iconic village, Stake is a modern take on the classic chophouse of decades past with a chef-driven menu sourced with only the highest quality ingredients available.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Chef de Cuisine Sergio Jimenez’s menu includes a number of share-friendly filets, chops, Japanese A5 wagyu, and dry-aged prime steak, an expansive selection of seafood appetizers including raw oysters from both East & West coasts, Alaskan King Crab, ice-cold shellfish & crudo, healthy salads, and rustic, wood fire-roasted side dishes, in addition to a handful of freshly composed seasonal seafood entrées.\u003cbr />\u003cbr />Stake Chophouse & Bar is the only restaurant in Coronado that received the Best of Award of Excellence from Wine Spectator for 6 years in a row! Our experienced sommeliers can help pair the perfect wines with your dish. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />- Daily Happy Hour: 4pm-6:30pm

name: The Smoking Goat Restaurant
description: We have expanded our outdoor dining areas to continue to provide you with a safe and memorable dining experience. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />The Smoking Goat is an award-winning California-French bistro located in the heart of North Park, San Diego.\u003cbr /> \u003cbr />Inspired by his European Farm-to-Table up-bringing and culinary training at Le Cordon Bleu Paris, Executive Chef and Owner Fred Piehl, marries classic French cuisine with the bounty of San Diego in a way that is rustic, yet refined, imaginative, yet unpretentious. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />The dinners served feature in-season local, sustainable and organic ingredients and provide guests with a unique culinary experience, reminiscent of the European countryside. \u003cbr />\u003cbr />Boasting an eclectic and carefully selected wine, beer, craft aperitifs and cocktail list with selections from both the old and new world, The Smoking Goat assures there is always the correct pairing available.\u003cbr />

name: Brigantine Coronado
description: A San Diego tradition since 1969

name: House of Blues Restaurant & Bar - San Diego
description: Discover authentic Southern-dining at House of Blues Restaurant and Bar. From the family style dishes and craft cocktails to the best in live music and folk art, House of Blues Restaurant & Bar delivers an unforgettable experience.

name: North Italia - Fashion Valley
description: At North, we focus on what we do best: Italian from scratch. Enjoy any of our handmade pastas and pizzas, created with seasonal ingredients and inventive flavors.  Or, try a different signature dish, prepared with our fresh flavors from the garden, farm, and sea. We’ve hand crafted seasonal cocktails that pair great with our food, creating a real modern Italia experiences perfect for any occasion.

name: King's Fish House - Mission Valley
address: 825 Camino de la Reina, San Diego, CA, 92108
description: We’ve been in restaurants a long time – three generations, to be precise – and we love seafood. With seafood there’s so much to be passionate about – the freshness, the flavor, the variety, and the surprise.\u003cbr /> \u003cbr />To create the ultimate seafood experience, we traveled down the highways and byways. We pulled up a seat, put on bibs, and soaked up the seafood experience: The no-name dishes with unforgettable flavor, the fresh-caught oysters and clams piled high, the hand-lettered specials on ancient chalkboards, and the savory simmer of every combination of spices imaginable.\u003cbr /> \u003cbr />The pleasure of preparing and sharing seafood was simple and genuine, and it brought out the best in everyone. Often, we felt as if we’d been welcomed into somebody’s home. \u003cbr /> \u003cbr />That’s what King’s Fish House is all about — and we’ve tried to bring all of these ideas together into one single, spectacular place, filled with camaraderie and celebration, and the things we love best. Welcome to the House that Seafood Built!\u003cbr />

name: Old Town Tequila Factory Restaurant & Cantina
description: Located across from Heritage Park overlooking San Diego's Historic Old Town the Old Town Tequila Factory Restaurant & Cantina is a panoramic spot to enjoy rooftop dining, great Margaritas and delicious authentic Mexican food prepared from old world recipes. \u003cbr />The Tequila Factory is open for Lunch, Dinner, Saturday & Sunday Best of Weekend Champagne Brunch and Happy Hour on the Tequila Terrace overlooking Old Town and the City Light below...We offer a variety of unique venues such as a Sports Bar, Cigar & Tequila Terrace and our Veranda del Sol.\u003cbr />Bring Friends, Family and Your Appetite to the uniquely San Diego Old Town Tequila Factory Restaurant & Cantina.  Always Free Parking.

name: Siamo Napoli
description: Specializing in Napolitano style pizza and pasta.  We focus on clean fresh ingredients that thrive in our home land and make simple foods the star. We have a full bar with hand crafted drinks and a range of wines from Napoli and beyond.

name: Westerly Public House
description: Westerly Public House is inspired by the culture, lifestyle, food, and beverage that connects San Diego to the eastern coast of Australia. San Diego and Sydney share warm, sunny weather year-round, and an appetite for quality coffee, craft cocktails, local craft beer and wine, and hearty, vibrant, eclectic, bright, rustic, and fresh cuisine that creatively showcases local produce. In Australia, enjoyment of food, drink, and the outdoor lifestyle blend together at laid back all-day cafés that populate the coastal cities. WPH brings this Cal-Aussie energy to Point Loma.

name: Nado Republic
description: YOUR LIVING ROOM AWAY FROM HOME\r\nEST. IN 2018 NADO REPUBLIC IS A PLACE WHERE YOU MEET WITH  FRIENDS , TASTE SOME WINE COMBINED WITH TRADITIONAL ITALIAN FOODS

name: Blanco Tacos + Tequila - Fashion Valley
description: Blanco is more than your typical Mexican restaurant, it‘s an escape from the ordinary, a happy hour hang out, a place to sit back, recharge and party. It’s a vacation in your neighborhood that helps you relax with your favorite people. For food, margaritas, and good times, Blanco is the perfect place to find your bliss.
